Hereâ€™s a **clean, modern setup** (compatible with Rails 7â€“8 in 2026) using **pure JavaScript + JSX** (**.js** files with JSX syntax, **no TypeScript** at all).

### 1. Create the Rails app (skip default JS)

```bash
rails new my_awesome_app --database=postgresql --skip-javascript
cd my_awesome_app
```

### 2. Add jsbundling-rails + esbuild

```bash
bundle add jsbundling-rails
bin/rails javascript:install:esbuild
```

This creates `package.json`, `.gitignore` updates, `bin/dev` support, etc.

### 3. Install React (JSX works out of the box with esbuild)

```bash
yarn add react react-dom
#               or npm install react react-dom
```

**No** `@types/*`, **no** `typescript`, **no** `.tsx` files â€” keep everything `.js`

### 4. Important: tell esbuild to treat .js files as JSX

Edit the `"build"` script in `package.json`:

```json
"scripts": {
  "build": "esbuild app/javascript/application.js --bundle --sourcemap --outdir=app/assets/builds --public-path=/assets --loader:.js=jsx",
  "build:watch": "esbuild app/javascript/application.js --bundle --sourcemap --outdir=app/assets/builds --public-path=/assets --loader:.js=jsx --watch"
}
```

The key part is `--loader:.js=jsx` â€” this is what enables JSX syntax inside `.js` files.

### 5. Create basic React entry point

`app/javascript/application.js`

```jsx
import React from "react";
import { createRoot } from "react-dom/client";

import App from "./components/App";

const rootElement = document.getElementById("root");
if (rootElement) {
  const root = createRoot(rootElement);
  root.render(<App />);
}
```

### 6. Create your first component

`app/javascript/components/App.js`

```jsx
import React from "react";

export default function App() {
  return (
    <div style={{ padding: "2rem", fontFamily: "system-ui, sans-serif" }}>
      <h1 style={{ color: "#0066cc" }}>Rails + React (JSX only) ðŸš€</h1>
      
      <p>Created on {new Date().toLocaleDateString()}</p>

      <button
        onClick={() => alert("It works!")}
        style={{
          padding: "0.8rem 1.6rem",
          fontSize: "1.1rem",
          backgroundColor: "#0066cc",
          color: "white",
          border: "none",
          borderRadius: "6px",
          cursor: "pointer",
        }}
      >
        Click me
      </button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 7. Mount point in layout

`app/views/layouts/application.html.erb`

Make sure it contains:

```erb
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>My Awesome App</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    <%= csp_meta_tag %>

    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "application", "data-turbo-track": "reload" %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag "application", "data-turbo-track": "reload", defer: true %>
  </head>

  <body>
    <%= yield %>

    <!-- React root mount point -->
    <div id="root"></div>
  </body>
</html>
```

### 8. Development workflow (recommended)

Create or use `Procfile.dev`:

```yaml
web: bin/rails server -p 3000
js:  yarn build:watch
```

Then start everything with one command:

```bash
bin/dev
# or   foreman start -f Procfile.dev   (if you prefer foreman)
```

Now visit http://localhost:3000 â€” you should see the React component.

### Folder structure suggestion (future-friendly, JSX-only)

```
app/
â”œâ”€â”€ javascript/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ application.js                # entry point
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ components/
