â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Button.js
â”‚   â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ Header.js
â”‚   â”‚   â””â”€â”€ shared/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ contexts/          (optional later)
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ hooks/             (custom hooks)
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ utils/
â””â”€â”€ views/
    â””â”€â”€ layouts/
        â””â”€â”€ application.html.erb
```

### Quick checklist â€” common next steps

| Want to add              | Command / note                                 |
|--------------------------|------------------------------------------------|
| Tailwind CSS             | `bundle add tailwindcss-rails`<br>`bin/rails tailwindcss:install` |
| Axios / fetch wrapper    | `yarn add axios`                               |
| React state (light)      | `yarn add zustand`                             |
| Data fetching            | `yarn add @tanstack/react-query`               |
| Routing (full SPA)       | `yarn add react-router-dom`                    |
| ESLint + Prettier        | `yarn add -D eslint prettier eslint-plugin-react eslint-plugin-react-hooks` |

This setup is **very lightweight**, fast to build (thanks to esbuild), and avoids all TypeScript complexity while still letting you write modern JSX.

Let me know if you want to add routing, API calls to Rails, authentication, Tailwind, component library, etc. â€” happy to extend this exact style. Good luck!